## 6. Accessibility & Performance Wins

### Accessibility

1. **Focus management on tool switch**: When user switches tools via keyboard shortcut, move focus to the toolbar button for screen reader announcement. Add `aria-live="polite"` to the status bar.

   **File**: `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.module.css` -- add to `.statusBar`:
   ```css
   /* No CSS change needed, add aria-live="polite" to JSX */
   ```

   **File**: `src/renderers/SvgCanvas.jsx` line 681:
   ```jsx
   <div className={styles.statusBar} role="status" aria-live="polite">
   ```

2. **Color contrast**: The `--color-text-tertiary` (#94989F) on `--color-panel-bg` (#F4F3F0) yields a contrast ratio of approximately 3.0:1, which fails WCAG AA for small text. Change to `#6E7280` (approximately 4.7:1).

   **File**: `src/styles/variables.css` line 14:
   ```css
   --color-text-tertiary: #6E7280;  /* was #94989F */
   ```

3. **Keyboard navigation in sidebar**: Sidebar items use `<div onClick>` (`Sidebar.jsx` lines 154-168) instead of `<button>`. These are not keyboard-focusable. Convert all `.item` divs to buttons with `role="option"` and `aria-selected`.

4. **Reduced motion**: Add `prefers-reduced-motion` support:

   **File**: `src/styles/global.css`:
   ```css
   @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
     *, *::before, *::after {
       animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
       transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
     }
   }
   ```

### Performance

1. **CSS `will-change` for animated elements**: Add to elements that animate frequently:

   **File**: `src/ui/Toolbar.module.css`:
   ```css
   .toolbar {
     will-change: auto; /* not needed, remove if present */
   }
   ```

   More importantly, add `contain: content` to sidebar sections and properties panel sections to limit layout recalculation scope:

   ```css
   .section { contain: content; }
   ```

2. **Reduce SVG re-renders**: The `cursorPos` state in `SvgCanvas.jsx` (line 73) triggers a full component re-render on every mouse move. The cursor position is only used in the status bar (lines 682-683). Move cursor display to a separate small component that subscribes to a ref-based value, preventing the entire SVG tree from re-rendering.

3. **Skeleton states for lazy-loaded 3D preview**: The current fallback (`App.module.css` `.previewFallback`, line 63) is a plain text label. Replace with an animated skeleton:

   ```css
   .previewFallback {
     background: var(--color-panel-bg);
     position: relative;
     overflow: hidden;
   }
   .previewFallback::after {
     content: '';
     position: absolute;
     inset: 0;
     background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, rgba(255,255,255,0.4), transparent);
     animation: shimmer 1.5s infinite;
   }
   @keyframes shimmer {
     0% { transform: translateX(-100%); }
     100% { transform: translateX(100%); }
   }
   ```

